What a total disappointment of a new restaurant. I sometimes wonder why these local restaurants don't bother trying. At least make as if you care for the first month that you open.  I walked in here one evening as I was starving and they were almost the only store open on the block. The decor is very pizza store type with bold yellow and red paint.  I walk up to the counter where a young guy, can't be older than 18 is chatting to his friends and practically ignoring that I'm ready to order. When I started asking him questions, mid question he would look away and respond to his friend. That, my friends, is beyond rude. That is just utterly awful behaviour.  So I finally order a personal pie and curly fries. I'm the only person in the store ordering, I think I waited more than 15 min for my order. (Red Flag 2)  I get home and open the pizza box. The pizza was so underwhelming, untasty, flat and way too much sauce to cheese ratio. It was dripping in tomato and a crust way too thick and tasteles. An absolute no no. I then open the curly fries --- lo and behold it's frozen fries. There was zero freshness to it.  I'm writing this place off as an absolute no. Spend your hard earned money elsewhere.
